--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages hping2.

hping2 is a network tool able to send custom TCP/IP packets and to display
target replies like ping do with ICMP replies. hping2 can handle fragmentation,
and almost arbitrary packet size and content, using the command line interface.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: hping2
    vars:
     hping2_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: hping2
    vars:
     hping2_state: 'remove'

INACTIVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: hping2
    vars:
     hping2_state: 'inactive'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  hping2_state
    Description: Control the state of the role.
    Implemented: 0.1
    Required   : False
    Value      : Predetermined
    Type       : String
    Default    : 'install'
    Options    :
      Install : 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
      Remove  : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'
      Inactive: 'quiesce' | 'inactive'

